its shopify

Thanks for letting me know you're using Shopify. To ensure your pixel is working correctly, make sure the customer event is properly configured in Shopify. You can test the event in both Shopify and NewsBreak to verify it triggers correctly. For a complete_payment event, simulate a product purchase to check the setup. If you need more detailed instructions, you can refer to our article on installing a NewsBreak Pixel on Shopify.
I tried a purchase but its still stuck

If your purchase event is still not registering, please double-check that the pixel code is correctly placed in the `theme.liquid` file of your Shopify store. Ensure it's just before the `</head>` tag. Also, verify that the custom event is set up correctly in Shopify and that it fires during a test purchase. If everything seems correct but it's still not working, you might want to reach out to adsupport@newsbreak.com for further assistance.

If you've done these steps and it's still not working, you might want to test the pixel using a browser extension like Facebook Pixel Helper to see if it's firing correctly.
